<div id="review_953807128" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/953807128" />
    <a title="Brigid ✩" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/886144-brigid"><img alt="Brigid ✩" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1581869052p2/886144.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/953807128?book_show_action=true">May 31, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brigid ✩" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brigid ✩" href="/user/show/886144-brigid">Brigid ✩</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/886144-brigid?shelf=middle-grade">middle-grade</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/886144-brigid?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/886144-brigid?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/886144-brigid?shelf=young-adult">young-adult</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/886144-brigid?shelf=mythology">mythology</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer953807128" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3755523059999256620">A friend gave this book to me like a year ago and then I found it recently and decided to read it on a super long bus ride. It was a pretty quick read and entertaining even though I&apos;m not an expert on Arthurian legend ... It held my attention most of the time and I did like it. But I don&apos;t know, it seemed to be missing something. It was written in a diary format which I always makes me feel kind of distant from the story/characters because it&apos;s just kind of like, &quot;Today this thing happened and t</span>
  <span id="freeText3755523059999256620" style="display:none">A friend gave this book to me like a year ago and then I found it recently and decided to read it on a super long bus ride. It was a pretty quick read and entertaining even though I'm not an expert on Arthurian legend ... It held my attention most of the time and I did like it. But I don't know, it seemed to be missing something. It was written in a diary format which I always makes me feel kind of distant from the story/characters because it's just kind of like, "Today this thing happened and that thing happened." So for the most part, the story felt more focused on summary. On top of that, I didn't find the narrative voice very strong or emotional, so I didn't connect with Arthur all that much. The pacing was also pretty slow ... There wasn't really much of a conflict or anything I found particularly exciting, and then at the end it just kind of faded out without much of a bang. I know it's part of a series, but I still would have liked more of a developed story arc and more of a sense of closure at the end. Over all, I liked it but probably not enough to move on to the sequel. </span>
  <a data-text-id="3755523059999256620" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review953807128">
