<div id="review_104382353" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/104382353" />
    <a title="Nina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2695465-nina"><img alt="Nina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1274114160p2/2695465.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/104382353?book_show_action=true">May 26, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nina" href="/user/show/2695465-nina">Nina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer104382353" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer102516555336334768">The story is set in medieval times, in 1199. It’s a story about a young boy called Arthur, that truly wants to be knight. One day he gets a magical stone from his fathers friend called Merlin. This magical stone takes Arthur in another world, the world where King Arthur lives. Arthur founds out that his life is little bit similar with the king, what a coincidence!<br/><br/>The story was so much fun to read. You really get to know Arthur and also his family. You get to love and hate some of them. The autho</span>
  <span id="freeText102516555336334768" style="display:none">The story is set in medieval times, in 1199. It’s a story about a young boy called Arthur, that truly wants to be knight. One day he gets a magical stone from his fathers friend called Merlin. This magical stone takes Arthur in another world, the world where King Arthur lives. Arthur founds out that his life is little bit similar with the king, what a coincidence!<br /><br />The story was so much fun to read. You really get to know Arthur and also his family. You get to love and hate some of them. The author really gives you good idea how a family could survived in the Medieval times. Also when you read the story, you feel like you’re really there in England and Wales.<br /><br />The book was easy to read and I recommend this to anyone who loves to read about medieval times and especially about King Arthur.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="102516555336334768" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


