  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2764128287" />
    <a title="Amber Scaife" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/64987691-amber-scaife"><img alt="Amber Scaife" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1524508473p2/64987691.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2764128287?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Amber Scaife" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Amber Scaife" href="/user/show/64987691-amber-scaife">Amber Scaife</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook 9780807205464" href="/book/show/9824935-the-seeing-stone">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2764128287" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4369316345421134423">A young Arthur living at the end of the twelfth century in England is given an obsidian stone by his father&apos;s friend, Merlin. In the stone, he sees the life of another, older Arthur, and their two lives are strangely similar.<br/>Meh. I couldn&apos;t get into this one much, although in general it was an okay read. I don&apos;t see the point of the link between the two Arthurs and that irritated me and spoiled the book for me a bit.</span>
  <span id="freeText4369316345421134423" style="display:none">A young Arthur living at the end of the twelfth century in England is given an obsidian stone by his father's friend, Merlin. In the stone, he sees the life of another, older Arthur, and their two lives are strangely similar.<br />Meh. I couldn't get into this one much, although in general it was an okay read. I don't see the point of the link between the two Arthurs and that irritated me and spoiled the book for me a bit.</span>
