        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3040395023" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1194509594950167693">This Middle Grade novel is an educational and entertaining read about a 13 year old boy named Arthur living on the border of England and Wales in AD 1199. It interweaves the story of King Arthur in its narrative about boy Arthur&apos;s everyday life, and although I&apos;m not really able to understand the connection and where Crossley-Holland is going with this yet, I can&apos;t wait to continue on with the second book in the trilogy.</span>
  <span id="freeText1194509594950167693" style="display:none">This Middle Grade novel is an educational and entertaining read about a 13 year old boy named Arthur living on the border of England and Wales in AD 1199. It interweaves the story of King Arthur in its narrative about boy Arthur's everyday life, and although I'm not really able to understand the connection and where Crossley-Holland is going with this yet, I can't wait to continue on with the second book in the trilogy.</span>
