<div id="review_2460217776" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2460217776" />
    <a title="Ashley Thacker" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/81327792-ashley-thacker"><img alt="Ashley Thacker" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2460217776?book_show_action=true">Jul 17, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ashley Thacker" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ashley Thacker" href="/user/show/81327792-ashley-thacker">Ashley Thacker</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/81327792-ashley-thacker?shelf=eng-356-reviews-13-25">eng-356-reviews-13-25</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2460217776" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12172224645837534225">Arthur, living during the turn of the 13th century, dreams of one thing: to become a squire and, eventually, a knight. Until now, however, his father hasn&apos;t allowed himself the opportunity. Then one day an old friend named Merlin (yes, <i>that</i> Merlin) give him a stone he calls a seeing stone and tells him to keep it secret. Through the stone, Arthur watches the story of King Arthur unfold, and quickly draws parallels to his daily life in the struggles he has with his own brother, his family, his fr</span>
  <span id="freeText12172224645837534225" style="display:none">Arthur, living during the turn of the 13th century, dreams of one thing: to become a squire and, eventually, a knight. Until now, however, his father hasn't allowed himself the opportunity. Then one day an old friend named Merlin (yes, <i>that</i> Merlin) give him a stone he calls a seeing stone and tells him to keep it secret. Through the stone, Arthur watches the story of King Arthur unfold, and quickly draws parallels to his daily life in the struggles he has with his own brother, his family, his friends, and his beliefs. Following a journal-like format, Arthur describes his thoughts and feelings as he struggles to overcome his challenges and achieve his dreams.<br /><br />Over all, I wasn't really impressed by this book. While it did sound just like a thirteen-year-old boy writing in a journal, I didn't feel like there was much of a plot to move the story forward. I wasn't really engaged most of the time and the only thing that really kept me going was a desire to know the secret that was mentioned in the first chapter of the story, but not revealed until the second to last chapter.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12172224645837534225" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


