<div id="review_413364124" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/413364124" />
    <a title="Antonia" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4742207-antonia"><img alt="Antonia" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1553197217p2/4742207.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/413364124?book_show_action=true">Sep 13, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Antonia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Antonia" href="/user/show/4742207-antonia">Antonia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780439263276" href="/book/show/444352.The_Seeing_Stone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4742207-antonia?shelf=i-own">i-own</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer413364124" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2091946622891051634">A book for kids, elementary until middle school age readers. I loved the fact that it was a take on King Arthur&apos;s stories and that it also included Merlin. There was also a fair proportion of magic and adventure in it. What I didn&apos;t like was the fact that it&apos;s supposed to be written like a journal, but it doesn&apos;t look like a journal at all. The chapters have no dates or titles or anything, and some of them look like totally separated journal entries. There were also these flash-backs that confus</span>
  <span id="freeText2091946622891051634" style="display:none">A book for kids, elementary until middle school age readers. I loved the fact that it was a take on King Arthur's stories and that it also included Merlin. There was also a fair proportion of magic and adventure in it. What I didn't like was the fact that it's supposed to be written like a journal, but it doesn't look like a journal at all. The chapters have no dates or titles or anything, and some of them look like totally separated journal entries. There were also these flash-backs that confused me to some extent.<br />Because the narrator is supposed to be a 13-year-old kid, the writing wasn't attractive to me. I hope it becomes more accurate and detailed in the next books, as he gets older.<br />Overall, a good read. 3 out of 5 stars and I recommend it to adventure and medieval book lovers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2091946622891051634" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


