        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2614974235" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17091523089976402891">The Seeing Stone is a story that I feel like I can’t even give a detailed review for. I thought the book was alright. The book was set like a diary where Arthur pretty much just tells recaps of his day. This proved to not be very entertaining as nothing of interest to me ever seemed to happen. Personally I am not the biggest fan of medieval elements, not to say I don’t like them. The plot felt bland and that bits of these were tossed in to try and make it a better read. Despite all of my critiqu</span>
  <span id="freeText17091523089976402891" style="display:none">The Seeing Stone is a story that I feel like I can’t even give a detailed review for. I thought the book was alright. The book was set like a diary where Arthur pretty much just tells recaps of his day. This proved to not be very entertaining as nothing of interest to me ever seemed to happen. Personally I am not the biggest fan of medieval elements, not to say I don’t like them. The plot felt bland and that bits of these were tossed in to try and make it a better read. Despite all of my critiques, the descriptions were very good and I was able to picture many of the scenes. Nevertheless, it is a book and not a picture, so that could only make up so much for the lack of action throughout the novel.</span>
