<div id="review_1250803621" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1250803621" />
    <a title="Isis" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/914674-isis"><img alt="Isis" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1203211958p2/914674.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1250803621?book_show_action=true">Apr 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Isis" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Isis" href="/user/show/914674-isis">Isis</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780439263269" href="/book/show/671720.The_Seeing_Stone">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/914674-isis?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/914674-isis?shelf=ya">ya</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/914674-isis?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1250803621" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5642417134748828825">Loved the concept, hated the style. Probably the most interesting bits to me were the details of English medieval life - the guisers on Hallowe&apos;en, the manor court, the Christmas celebration, the remedies for illness and injury. Arthur himself was not particularly engaging, and the parallel stories ought to have appealed to me but didn&apos;t. As Arthuriana it falls far short, and as a YA story about a medieval boy it moves too slowly. Not inclined to pick up the rest of the trilogy.</span>
  <span id="freeText5642417134748828825" style="display:none">Loved the concept, hated the style. Probably the most interesting bits to me were the details of English medieval life - the guisers on Hallowe'en, the manor court, the Christmas celebration, the remedies for illness and injury. Arthur himself was not particularly engaging, and the parallel stories ought to have appealed to me but didn't. As Arthuriana it falls far short, and as a YA story about a medieval boy it moves too slowly. Not inclined to pick up the rest of the trilogy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5642417134748828825" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

