<div id="review_1124578920" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1124578920" />
    <a title="Elea" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/37661183-elea"><img alt="Elea" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1124578920?book_show_action=true">Dec 06, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elea" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elea" href="/user/show/37661183-elea">Elea</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1124578920" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12359647806140861754">This book was quite good. At the beginning I hated it and by the end it was ok. I liked the idea of the story recreating King Arthur’s legend. We get to see a lot of Arthur’s life in the middle ages so the visions make it more interesting. Although there are some moments of confusion, the research done by the author to find all the information needed to recreate a middle ages life is very good. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

